🎁 It's Christmas time and the holidays can be a very hard time for many people. Can I challenge you to truly love on people this season? Not just those that can reciprocate, but those that have nothing to offer you in return. Let it be said that we infected this world with the Love of God in such a way that it helped propel people forward 🙏🏼

💙 Raising my son has helped me realize the powerful impact love has on a person. Seeing how love from my husband and I affects his behavior and development is truly incredible!!! We are licensed foster parents and it's gut-wretching to see that neglected children are delayed in their development. Everytime I hold Elionaijah I think of how his life is being shaped by the relationships he has with those around him even from this young of an age. I see how love affects us all regardless how young or old. My Christmas mood is going to be to spread love - like they say "That's the Brooklyn way" 😉

2022 ended in a way that kinda shook some of the things I believed about myself. It was a combination of being disappointed about the things I wasn't able to get done, the lack of support I felt from different areas in my life and then the enemy used people I thought I respected to straight assault my character (wouldn't be the first time this happened to me) never the less, I was blind sided and already super emotionally vulnerable so it rocked the ship, so to speak. 

"What's wrong with me?" Those were the lyrics of song I wrote that just kept lingering in my soul. 

This year, I began 2023 with a fast to help clear my mind and heart and really hear from God. What He said was something I wasn't expecting, I had allowed external things to impact my belief about identity. Jesus wasn't looking for bad things to point out about me and needed to be fixed, He was just singing back to me - "Nothing is wrong with you, I love you, you are my beloved 😭"

I wanted to share this with you because maybe you forgot as well, just how valuable you are to your Creator, How loved you are by Him and have allowed the noise of this world to rob you of the truth. Well, there is no time like now to pivet and embrace what God says ❤️

“For as high as the heavens are above the earth, so great is his love for those who fear him; as far as the east is from the west, so far has he removed our transgressions from us.” – Psalms 103:11-12

“Therefore, there is now no condemnation for those who are in Christ Jesus, because through Christ Jesus the law of the Spirit who gives life has set you free from the law of sin and death.” – Romans 8:1-2

Comments below with some other scriptures that show you how God feels about you 👇🏼

#identity #Godslove #IamwhoyousayIam

💙 Israel 💙

Being in the Holy Land during Holy Week really cemented my faith! I'm still processing everything that I feel but honestly, Israel made everything so real to me. I'm more in love with Jesus than ever ❤️

I loved experiencing this with my husband and son and we really all felt at home, as crazy as that sounds. From Galilee to Solomon's temple in Jerusalem, to the Dead Sea, to the Mount of Olives, everything was a magical experience. Walking where Jesus did was breathtaking and I was most surprised by how the language used in the Bible to describe the areas of the land is still relevant today. 

I learned so much and understand the Jewish culture much greater, as we were immersed in the culture. What you don't see here, is that we had the honor of spending Passover with an orthodox Jewish Rabbi and his super awesome wife (That was amazing)!!! I'll never forget that! I respect the dedication they have to their faith.

I also enjoyed chatting with our Muslim drivers (When all transportation shut down for Pesach and Sabbat lol) and learning what they really believe about Christ. I loved that everyone thought hubby and I were Arabic 💕 

I was shocked at how religious everyone was. Everywhere we went, people were reading the Torah, or holding their rope Muslim beads, or worshiping Jesus out loud!!! I was surprised to see everyone do what they do regardless of who was around. I think sometimes we Westerners have a perception of everyone in Israel hating each other so much that they do not even coexist (but that's not true). Just walk from gate to gate of the Old City to see for yourself.

Yes while we were there, the city was on high alert (With police packing AKs everywhere) as missiles were being launched at Israel but I guess growing up in the hood of NYC prepared me to always be on high alert. So we were ok lol 

With all my mind and heart I feel Israel is where God dwells 😭 I can not wait to return ❤️ 

Ask me questions if you'd like I'm open to sharing more xoxo

#Israel #jerusalem #holyland 

P.S. Background song by Joshua Aaron "The Blessing (Hebrew version) Pray for the peace of Israel 🙏

You don't often hear about mom guilt...

The times I'm working on something but my heart wants to be with my little love, watching his brain develop as he discovers something new so often, or when I'm writing or reading but I could be teaching him a new life skill instead. Tomorrow I leave on a work trip and it takes everything in me to not ask if I can bring him along lol under 2 years old fly for free 😅 But it's not practical at all how would I get any work done? The trips will just continue coming this year as well and  I worry about how smooth things will go when I'm not home, I get sad about not putting him to sleep at night, or feeding him, or dancing together like total goof balls 🕺💃

Then I wish the house would be cleaner, or I wonder if the fridge is stocked enough... etc the list goes on. 

But then I stop and thank God - 1. That I have Him (He allowed me to hold this miracle baby in my arms even though his brothers and sister are in heaven) 2. God has blessed my hubby and I with jobs to provide a roof over our heads, food and clothes and lastly 3. It's OK to feel these very human feelings while still being enough, and everything Elionaijah needs in his mother 💕

I wrote this post for anyone else who knows what I'm talking about 💐 You are an incredible mom! Your kids are blessed to have you!

At the end of last year, I felt God put it on my heart that I was to make a new album. Since then, I've been writing and slowly recording. Slowly? Why?? Because it takes money and the money I earn now goes to paying my mortgage and taking care of my family 🙏🏼

In times past, when I've recorded records, I was either signed to a major label, or someone generously donated into my work. Recently, so many of my friends have asked me why don't you just raise money for an album? I hate asking for those kinds of things 🥺 however, I do believe a new album, with honest, heart felt and bumping music is what God asked me to do..... So.... if you've ever believed in my music, have been inspired by it, or simply just believe in giving to things that help bring hope to the world, I'll be so appreciative of your contribution. Transition can make way for insecurities. 

I've always been pretty confident. When I was younger, I was confident in myself, then in my talent, then Jesus got a hold of me and I became confident in God and who I am in Him. That truth about me hasn't changed, but I've noticed that transition has a way of rocking your foundation if you don't commit to letting Gods truth be your solid ground. 

In this new season, I'm a wife, mom, foster mom, working woman, minister, performer, journalist ... 😅 etc and although I've worn some of these hats for some time, I've never been all of them at once and at the top of this year, I found myself not as emotionally stable as I'm use to. I'm super hard on myself, so for a while, I couldn't figure out what was wrong. Sure I had a few disappointments and a few people even assassinate my character but that's nothing new 🙃 Then it hit me, I'm still trying to find my footing in this season and those transitions have affected my confidence. 

Realizing that has helped me refocus and seek God in all this. I wrote all this to encourage anyone else who may be feeling insecure or not settled in themselves. Seasons of transition do that to us. Our part is to seek the true constant in it all, God! He knows us, He loves us, He's picked us, and He's our firm foundation ❤️ 

Don't let changes, change you, you got this because God's got you 💪🏼‼️
